# Facial Recognition Attendance System

This is the final year project by **Shreyash Ghale** for Islington College and London Metropolitan University. It is a full-stack facial recognition-based attendance system that combines React (Vite) frontend, Node.js Express backend, and a Python Flask service for facial detection.

---
# For frontend install the following:
    cd frontend/my-react-app
    npm install       # or yarn
    npm run dev

# For backend
    cd backend
    npm install
    npm start

# for python (/backend-p)

    Pre-requisites for Windows
    Desktop development with C++ in Visual studio must be installed for dlib to be compined
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    python server.python

# create the .evn file with the following details
    DB_HOST="localhost"
    DB_USER="root"
    DB_PASSWORD=""
    DB_NAME="fras_fyp"
    PORT=3000
    JWT_KEY="jwt-secret-key"

# For database, mysql is used
    install xaamp 
    and create a database named "fras_fyp"
    then import the database provided in database folder
